          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">2.</span>More bioavailable than plain L-tyrosine.</h4><p>The N-acetyl form is more soluble than standard L-tyrosine, which makes it easier for the body to absorb and use.</p></div>
          <div class="point"><h4><span class="point-num">3.</span>Supports cognition under cognitive demand.</h4><p>Research suggests NALT is most useful when the brain is depleting catecholamines faster than usual, such as during long stretches of focus, stress, or fatigue.</p></div>
